    <div id="main">
		<h1>My Parent element is a div</h1>
		<p class="main-content">All the elements contained within the surrounding div element are siblings.</p> 
		<p class="main-content">Which also means all the elements within this div elements  are children of the div element</p>
	</div>
	<section>
		<h1 class="section-header">My parent element is a Section</h1>
		<p class="section-content">The section element is the next sibling element of the div element.The div element is the previous sibling element of the section</p>
		<p class="section-content">The h1 element and the three paragraphs in this section element are its children elements</p>
		<p class="section-content">The h1 element and the three paragraphs are siblings</p>
	</section>
    
